longing, remake intimate relations, and negotiate opportunities and constraints across borders. The interplay between migration and time shapes the ways aging migrant populations reassess and reconstruct relationships with their children, spouses, grandchildren, community members, and home, as well as host societies. Aging, Sun argues, is a global issue and must be reconsidered in a cross-border environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGenerationsxSocial aspects. 0aOld agexSocial aspects. 0aOlder Asian AmericansxSocial conditionsy21st century. 0aOlder immigrantsxFamily relationships. 0aTaiwanesezUnited StatesxSocial conditionsy21st century. 4aAsian Studies. 4aFamily & Relationships. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aAging and migration, Transnational Migration, Diaspora and homeland, taiwanese immigrants,.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501754883?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501754883423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501754883/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2